an>Standards &amp; compliance</span></h4><ul><li>BS EN 50173 / TIA-568 — structured cabling</li><li>BS 6701 — cabling installation &amp; safety</li><li>CDM 2015 across every package</li></ul></div></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">FAQs</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Your questions,<br>answered.</h2></div><div class="faq reveal in"><details class="faq-item"><summary>Is the cabling tested and certified?</summary><p>Yes. Structured cabling is installed and tested to BS EN 50173 and BS 6701, with full test results and as-built records handed over.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you fit out comms rooms?</summary><p>Yes. We deliver comms rooms end to end — racks, containment, fibre backbones and the resilient power the equipment needs.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Can you coordinate data with the rest of the MEPH package?</summary><p>Yes. Delivering data alongside power, mechanical and public health means the containment and supplies are coordinated by one accountable team.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Which areas do you cover?</summary><p>London and the South East, including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire.</p></details></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">Part of MEPH</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Explore the full<br>package.</h2></div><div class="sectorrow reveal in"><a class="sector" href="/meph/">MEPH overview</a><a class="sector" href="/meph/mechanical-hvac/">Mechanical &amp; HVAC</a><a class="sector" href="/meph/electrical/">Electrical</a><a class="sector" href="/meph/public-health/">Public Health</a></div></section><section class="sec tight line-top"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><div class="kicker">The other three lines</div><h2 class="dhead sm">One contractor,<br>four service lines.</h2></div><div class="otherlines reveal 